		<node ID="ID_477643513" LINK="http://cs-fundamentals.com/tech-interview/c/difference-between-static-and-dynamic-linking.php" TEXT="Difference Between Static and Dynamic Library Linking">
			<node ID="ID_694919431" TEXT="This page explains the difference between static and dynamic linking of libraries. The difference between static and dynamic (shared) link libraries is that static libraries are linked at compile time while dynamica libraries are linked at run time by loader. Dynamic linking offers several advantages over static linking." />
			</node>
		<node ID="ID_1318250306" LINK="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Static_library" TEXT="Static library - Wikipedia">
			<node ID="ID_558479477" TEXT="Static library files may be linked at run time by a linking loader (e.g. the X11 module loader). However whether such a process can be called static linking is controversial. Creating static libraries in C/C++. Static libraries can be easily created in C or in C++." />
