			<node ID="ID_937067215" TEXT="What is a real-time operating system (RTOS)? A real-time operating system or RTOS is a system installed within your production or operating environment to gather and synthesize information as it comes in. It connects related terminals or points of entry to create a network or a central point where all your operations can be monitored." />
