			<node ID="ID_1860771834" TEXT="Business process management is neither task management (which focuses on individual tasks) or project management (which handles one-time or unpredictable flows). Task management is about handling or organizing a set of activities that arise out of a project. These projects are often one-time and non-repeatable." />
