			<node ID="ID_160964696" TEXT="Types of CPU Scheduling. CPU scheduling decisions may take place under the following four circumstances: When a process switches from the running state to the waiting state(for I/O request or invocation of wait for the termination of one of the child processes).; When a process switches from the running state to the ready state (for example when an interrupt occurs)." />
