			<node ID="ID_1555557128" TEXT="Processor Scheduling (or CPU Scheduling) determines which processes are assigned to and removed from the CPU based on scheduling models such as Preemptive and Non-Preemptive Scheduling (also known as Co-operative Scheduling).. Older systems could operate in simple stand-alone modes but with the increasing need for responsive flexible systems as well as virtualization managing multi " />
