		<node ID="ID_882691431" LINK="https://techdifferences.com/difference-between-paging-and-segmentation-in-os.html" TEXT="Difference Between Paging and Segmentation in OS (with ">
			<node ID="ID_1758421879" TEXT="The basic difference between paging and segmentation is that &#8220;page&#8221; is a fixed-sized block whereas a &#8220;segment&#8221; is a variable-sized block. We will discuss some more differences between Paging and Segmentation with the help of comparison chart shown below. Content: Paging Vs Segmentation. Comparison Chart;" />
			</node>
		<node ID="ID_802940323" LINK="https://www.gatevidyalay.com/segmentation-and-paging-segmented-paging/" TEXT="Segmentation and Paging | Segmented Paging | Gate Vidyalay">
			<node ID="ID_1569999191" TEXT="Segmented Paging in OS is a scheme that implements the combination of segmentation and paging. Segmentation and Paging are non-contiguous memory allocation techniques." />
			</node>
		<node ID="ID_91543788" LINK="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c5bKqbbyIq4" TEXT="Segmentation with Paging H/W Support Diagram and Solved ">
